Dear NFV friends,
<br><br>

Is it just me or can you feel a new wind blowing over the NFV community?
 There is a different energy in the air as we are starting 2015. 
<br><br>
VNF vendors need to achieve NFV maturity and be able to prove their 
capabilities. Service Providers need to evolve their network and IT 
organizations towards unified teams and processes; Network solution 
providers like ALU need to redefine without compromising the carrier 
grade excellence our customers expect from us. 
<br><br>
This month’s newsletter illustrates just that. Portugal Telecom Inovacao
 shares with us their NFV vision. Guy Shemesh reports real life customer
 conversations and Ron Haberman redefines the MANO in a very concrete 
way. 
<br><br>
Enjoy, and let's continue the great work!<br>
Valerie &amp; team



