<b>Demystifying the MANO, Ron Haberman at Carrier Network Virtualization</b>
</center>
<br><br>
We recently took part in the Carrier Network Virtualization event in 
Palo Alto where Ron Haberman, CloudBand's GM gave a session focused on 
"Demystifying the MANO” - as operators continue their aggressive plans 
for NFV, the attention is now on the management and orchestration layer,
 called MANO in ETSI NFV. The role of MANO is causing some confusion in 
the industry as it’s not clearly defined and yet it plays a critical 
role in making NFV a reality. In this presentation Ron helps demystify 
the role of MANO by addressing some key questions.  
